column5: AFTER ALL THAT RAIN AND MELTING SNOW THE WATER LEVELS IN THE TRIBS STILL DROPPED VERY FAST . WATERS ARE STILL VERY VERY LOW. BEEN OUT A FEW TIMES THIS WEEK AND SEEMED TO ALWAYS BE AT THE WRONG PLACE AT THE WRONG TIME!! GOOD NUMBERS WERE BEING CAUGHT AT DIFFERENT TRIBS ALL ON DIFFERENT DAYS  LOL CAUGHT ALOT OF DINKERS AND PULLED THIS NICE HEN FROM UNDER A TREE THE OTHER DAY!!!   JUST GOTTA KEEP AT IT LOL
CC She is a beauty, nice and silver. I have got to get out soon.
Glad to see you back on the board again Scott.
Nice...blends in well with the snowy icy ground.  bbbbrrrrrr
Everyone misses once and a while, nice fish.
good work, thats a sweet steelie
